{"word":"H1897 - הָגָה - hâgâh - daw-gaw' - Imagine","slug":"H1897","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">הָגָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>hâgâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-gaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Imagine"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D4;&#x05D2;&#x05D4; - ha&#x0302;ga&#x0302;h</b> - <i>haw-gaw'</i><p/>A primitive root (compare <a href=\"#/H1901\">H1901</a>); to <i>murmur</i> (in pleasure or anger); by implication to <i>ponder: - </i>imagine, meditate, mourn, mutter, roar, X sore, speak, study, talk, utter."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1899\">H1899</a>, <a href=\"#/H1900\">H1900</a>, <a href=\"#/H1902\">H1902</a>"}]}